chmod               - all related to permission u/g/o(others) +r/w/x filename - 7 = 4+2+1 (read/write/execute)
cmp                 - This utility compares two files of any type and writes the results to the standard output .e.g. cmp file1.txt file2.txt
chown               - file ownership $USER:$USERGRP -R(recursive for folder files) filename/foldername
comm                - It compares common lines of file1 and file2 . E.g. comm -12 a.txt b.txt
df                  - Show the amount of disk space used on each mounted filesystem.
less                - Similar to the more command, but the user can page up and down through the file
ln                  - Creates a symbolic link to a file.
locate              - A fast database driven file locator.
rm -- "-filename"   - to delete file that starts with - symbol. 
more                - Allows file contents or piped output to be sent to the screen one page at a time.
whereis             - Show where the binary, source and manual page files are for a command
vmstat              - it reports information about processes, memory, paging, block IO, traps, and cpu activity.
grep                - This searches the named input FILEs (or standard input if no files are named, or the file name - is given) for lines containing a match to the given PATTERN. 
awk                 - This is linux program mostly used for pattern scanning and processing. It searches one or more files to see if they contain lines that matches with the specified patterns and then perform associated actions.
              awk '/search pattern1/ {Actions}
                   /search pattern2/ {Actions}' file

              - example
                    $ awk 'BEGIN {print "Name\tDesignation\tDepartment\tSalary";}
                      > {print $2,"\t",$3,"\t",$4,"\t",$NF;}                                 # here $2 , $3 etc are column number
                      > END{print "Report Generated\n--------------";
                      > }' employee.txt
                      Name	Designation	Department	Salary
                      Thomas 	 Manager 	 Sales 	         $5,000
                      Jason 	 Developer 	 Technology 	 $5,500
                      Sanjay 	 Sysadmin 	 Technology 	 $7,000
                      Nisha 	 Manager 	 Marketing 	 $9,500
                      Randy 	 DBA 	 	 Technology 	 $6,000
                      Report Generated
Gawk                - This is the GNU Project's version of the AWK programming language.
bzip2               - A portable, fast, open source program used to compress and decompress files at a high rate









